The paper proposes a novel technique for constrained submodular maximization, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and optimization. The paper also extensively evaluates the proposed algorithm over several real-world applications, indicating a strong focus on practical applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) and social and information networks (cs.SI) due to the real-world applications mentioned.
